body:
> Is this a missing intercept point? 

Yes

> What is the case we need this, and existing interceptors are not supported?

As shown below, in ```HttpHandler#handleRequest(HttpServerExchange)```, an asynchronous task can be submitted through ```HttpServerExchange#dispatch(Executor, Runnable)```
 and this interception was previously missing.
```
        Undertow server = Undertow.builder()
            .addHttpListener(8080, "0.0.0.0")
            .setHandler(exchange -> {
                exchange.dispatch(new HttpHandler() {
                    @Override
                    public void handleRequest(HttpServerExchange httpServerExchange) throws Exception {
                        // do something async
                    }
                });
                exchange.dispatch(new Runnable() {
                    @Override
                    public void run() {
                        // do something  async
                    }
                });
                exchange.getResponseHeaders().put(Headers.CONTENT_TYPE, "text/plain");
                exchange.getResponseSender().send("Success");
            }).build();
        server.start();
```
